==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|abisme|lang=fro}} (whence also French {{term|abîme|lang=fr}}) from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|abyssimus|lang=la}}, a superlative of {{term|abyssus|lang=la}} from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ἄβυσσος|tr=abussos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/əˈbɪzəm/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[abyss]]; a gulf, a [[chasm]], a very deep hole
